This HLS design sorts a small array of numbers that are passed by value using a
naive comparison-sort to compare all numbers to all other numbers.

To compile and simulate on Linux, use

make tutorial-fpga
./tutorial-fpga

To compile and simulate on Windows, use

build.bat
tutorial-fpga.exe

To compile and emulate on Linux, use

make tutorial-fpga DEVICE=x86-64
./tutorial-fpga

To compile and emulate on Windows, use

build.bat default x86-64
tutorial-fpga.exe

This tutorial requires the following tools to be installed:
  - Intel(R) High Level Synthesis (HLS) Compiler
  - Platform Designer
  - Intel Quartus Prime Pro Edition